Hurricane Harvey authored unwelcome chapters in the lives of thousands of families.
Mickel Batts is a Houston father who was forced to flee fast-rising water with five children in tow.
John Cservek and his wife, Kathy, saw their dream house in suburban Spring devastated only a little over a year after they bought it.
Judy Mellon is a veteran of past floods in Houston’s Meyerland neighborhood, but Harvey makes her wonder whether she can ever go home.
Beverly Bugler lived for years next to twin reservoirs that were usually dry until Harvey arrived. After fleeing the storm, she’s not so sure she wants to stay.
Now they all wonder about rebuilding and worry about what comes next.
